    content: `
      <h2>The True Cost of Poorly Managed Google Ads</h2>
      <p>Many businesses are unknowingly wasting 40-60% of their Google Ads budget on irrelevant clicks, broad match overkill, and poor landing page alignment. The good news? These are all fixable problems.</p>

      <h2>Smart Bidding Strategies That Actually Work</h2>
      <p>Automated Smart Bidding has matured significantly. Target CPA (cost per acquisition) and Target ROAS (return on ad spend) bidding strategies use machine learning to optimize bids in real time — but they require sufficient conversion data to work effectively.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Need at least 30-50 conversions/month for Target CPA to work well</li>
        <li>Start with Maximize Conversions while building conversion history</li>
        <li>Set realistic CPA targets based on your actual conversion data</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Keyword Match Type Strategy</h2>
      <p>The death of Broad Match Modified has changed the landscape. Use Exact Match for high-intent, proven keywords. Phrase Match for moderate control. Broad Match only with Smart Bidding and strong negative keyword lists.</p>

      <h2>Negative Keywords: Your Secret Weapon</h2>
      <p>A robust negative keyword list can cut wasted spend by 20-30%. Regularly review your Search Terms report to identify irrelevant queries. Build shared negative keyword lists across campaigns for efficiency.</p>

      <h2>Ad Copy That Converts</h2>
      <p>Responsive Search Ads (RSAs) are now the standard. Write 15 varied headlines and 4 descriptions that speak to different user intents. Use ad customizers for dynamic, relevant messaging. Test continuously.</p>

      <h2>Landing Page Alignment</h2>
      <p>Your Quality Score is heavily influenced by landing page relevance and user experience. Create dedicated landing pages for each ad group. Match the language of your ads. Make the conversion action obvious and frictionless.</p>

      <h2>Audience Layering for Better Targeting</h2>
      <p>Overlay audience segments — remarketing lists, customer match, similar audiences, in-market audiences — on your campaigns to adjust bids and messaging for higher-value users.</p>

      <h2>Measuring What Matters</h2>
      <p>Import Google Analytics 4 goals into Google Ads. Set up conversion tracking for all meaningful actions: form submissions, phone calls, chat starts, and purchases. Never optimize for vanity metrics.</p>

      <h2>Conclusion</h2>
      <p>A well-managed Google Ads account is one of the highest-ROI channels available to businesses. Regular optimization, honest attribution, and continuous testing separate profitable campaigns from budget drains.</p>
    `,
